{"key":"post-17860278","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17860278</id>\n<content>You might want to get the basics down first.&amp;nbsp; Brown rice flour is universally known as the fastest way to get from spores to fruits, bar none.&amp;nbsp; In speed, it will outperform rice bran or any other substrate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Minerals in bird seed and other grains do not impede colonization.&amp;nbsp; We actually add minerals(gypsum) to our grains.&amp;nbsp; Mg does impede colonization so we never use dolomite lime products.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's a mistake to think in terms of 'nutrition' ala botany and apply it to fungi which have different requirements.&amp;nbsp; For example the largest &lt;i&gt;P cubensis&lt;/i&gt; mushrooms you'll ever see will be grown on straw which is one of the &lt;i&gt;least nutritious&lt;/i&gt; substrates we have.&amp;nbsp; Shiitake growers supplement their sawdust with a bit of rice, wheat or oat bran, but if we overdo it by even a small amount, they only form mutants and no real fruits.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17860346</next>\n<prev>17860210</prev>\n<first>17859592</first>\n<last>17863291</last>\n<when>1361764967</when>\n<utime>02/25/13 06:02 AM</utime>\n</post>"}